{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 16:01:29.576933", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [host_2_1_1_1]\n- root_cause_name: [host_incorrect_gateway]\n\nRationale (from provided diagnosis):\n- Host 10.2.1.10 (host_2_1_1_1) configured default gateway 10.2.1.254, which is not present on the LAN (router_dist_2_1 is 10.2.1.1).\n- Host ARP for 10.2.1.254 fails; router can reach the host locally but off-subnet hosts cannot, indicating asymmetric routing / reply failure.\n- Conclusion: incorrect gateway configured on the host is the direct root cause of off-subnet reachability failures.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2170, "output_tokens": 165, "total_tokens": 2335, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
